benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/customFields/{customFieldId}/auditLogsWithHistory - Retrieve custom field audit logs with history by id

covered: GET • Valid Request: Successful retrieval with 200 and application/json (TC01).
GET • Empty Response: Returns 200 with empty JSON array when no logs (TC02).
GET • Authorization: 401 for missing/invalid token (TC06, TC07).
Robust 404 handling: Non-existent custom field and orphaned account (TC03, TC04, TC10, TC15, TC17).
Input validation: Invalid UUID format → 400; malformed/extra path segments handled (TC05, TC10, TC15, TC17).
Security hardening: SQL injection payload safely handled without information leakage (TC09).
Reliability/perf: Large dataset response and perf checks; concurrent requests covered (TC11, TC14).
Resilience: Backend outage returns 503 with safe error body (TC08).
Regression coverage: Known previous issues and backward compatibility (TC12, TC13).
gaps: GET • Pagination: No scenarios verifying pagination behavior for large audit log sets (if supported).
GET • Rate Limiting: No tests for throttling/429 when sending bursts beyond limits.
GET • Caching Behavior: No validation of ETag/Last-Modified, Cache-Control, or conditional requests (If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since).
Authorization granularity: No 403 Forbidden scenario for authenticated but unauthorized users (if RBAC applies).
Schema validation depth: Tests assert presence of required fields but do not validate full AuditLog schema/field types or order/format.
Content negotiation: No checks for Accept header variants or charset (e.g., application/json; charset=utf-8).
Observability: No verification that responses omit sensitive headers/body details beyond TC09 (e.g., correlation IDs present, no stack traces in general errors).
Error spectrum: Only 503 covered; no generic 5xx handling (e.g., 500) to ensure proper fallback behavior.
recommendations: Add pagination tests: request first/next pages, boundaries (page size limits), and validate total counts/links; or explicitly document N/A if endpoint is unpaginated.
Add rate limiting tests: exceed allowed RPS and verify 429, Retry-After header, and that normal traffic resumes afterward.
Add caching tests: verify ETag/Last-Modified and Cache-Control; send conditional GETs to validate 304 Not Modified and cache revalidation.
Include a 403 scenario if RBAC applies: authenticated user without permission cannot access another account’s custom field logs.
Strengthen schema checks: validate AuditLog object against full contract (types, required/optional fields, enums, timestamps format, history structure).
Test content negotiation: send Accept: application/json, text/plain, */* and verify correct behavior and 406 if unsupported.
Extend 5xx coverage: simulate generic server error (500) to confirm safe, consistent error payload without internal details.
Validate headers/observability: assert no sensitive headers exposed; optionally assert presence of correlation/request IDs for tracing.
Document non-applicable items (e.g., query parameters) in the feature to clarify scope and avoid ambiguity.
